premise_source_doc_sentence: The British Empire comprised the dominions , colonies , protectorates , mandates and other territories ruled or administered by the United Kingdom and its predecessor states .

claim: The British Empire included dominions, colonies, and protectorates.
premise_source_doc_sentence: In legal terms the territories included those formally under the sovereignty of the British monarch  (  who held the additional title of Empress  (  or Emperor  )  of India from 1876 to 1947  )  ; various `` foreign '' territories controlled as protectorates ; territories transferred to British administration under the authority of the League of Nations or the United Nations ; and miscellaneous other territories , such as Anglo-Egyptian Sudan .

premise_source_doc_sentence: A number of countries  (  `` dominions ''  )  within the British Empire gained independence in stages during the earlier part of the 20th century .

premise_source_doc_sentence: When the United Kingdom declared war on Nazi Germany at the outset of World War II it controlled to varying degrees numerous crown colonies , protectorates and the Indian Empire .
